d, Somerset, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Alford","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["habitational name from any of various places called Alford, for example in Somerset, Cheshire and Lincolnshire. The first is named with the Old English female personal name <i>Ealdgȳth</i> + <i>ford</i> ‘ford’. See also   Alvord  .","variant of   Halford   (or vice versa).","English:"],"variants":[{"name":"Alvord","meanings":["English (southwestern): variant of   Alford   1; the spelling reflects the southwestern English dialect pronunciation.","History: This surname was brought to North America by Alexander Alvord, who came from Devon or Somerset to Windsor, CT, <i>c.</i> 1645. He had many prominent descendants."]},{"name":"Halford","meanings":["English (mainly Midlands): habitational name from any of various places called Halford. Most, for example those in Warwickshire, Devon, and Shropshire, or the lost place <i>Haleford</i> in Pembury (Kent), are named from Old English <i>halh</i> ‘nook, recess’ + <i>ford</i> ‘ford’.","English: variant of   Alford   with prosthetic <i>H-</i>."]},{"name":"Allford","meanings":["English: variant of   Alford  ."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["form of   John  , also used quite frequently in the English-speaking world. In Northern Ireland it is sometimes found as a variant of   Ewan ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When John Alford was born in 1475, in Whitestaunton, Somerset, England, his father, Thomas Alford, was 20 and his mother, Mary de Vere, was 20. He married Agnes Hannah in 1505, in Whitestaunton, Somerset, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1530, in Whitestaunton, Somerset, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 55, and was buried in Chard, Somerset, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1475–1530":"1475–1530","1485–1